<br>
Please note:  This ONLY refers to raiding scenarios when there's fairly large numbers of people engaging a LOT of high aggro behaviour from a distance.  It does NOT refer to experience groups, more melee oriented raids, or anything else whuch doesn't involve high distance aggro.<br>
<br>
1. It is absolutely proven beyond a shadow of a doubt that one can be highest on a mob's aggro list and not be getting beaten upon because of distance.   Don't believe me?   Go get yourself on top of a mob's hate list with 10 mother melees around and try to move the mob.  You CANT DO IT by yourself unless it's immediately post-summon.<br>
<br>
2. IF you are the main tank and are NOT highest on the mob's hate list, but are the highest among those within &quot;aggro proximity&quot;, then a successful taunt ABSOLUTELY adds numeric hate to you, it places you above those higher than you yet far enough away to avoid engagement.<br>
<br>
3. Every time you press the taunt button, it does NOT guarantee a successful taunt.<br>
<br>
4. The more times you press it, the more likely it is to be successful once.<br>
<br>
5. If someone exceeds the range/aggro quotient, the mob WILL move, particularly post summonning placing everyone nearby in danger of either AE's or Melee damage.<br>
<br>
6. It is MUCH harder to re-establish lost aggro than it is to maintain a position on top of the aggro list.<br>
<br>
7. It is also MUCH less likely that a mob will be in taunt range for your convenience if he runs halfway across a zone to pound on a mage or wizard, leading to the possibility of wasting your chance to taunt because of range issues.<br>
<br>
8. If you think that you're on top of the mob's aggro list simply because he's beating on you, explain that to the wizards who get summonned while you're getting beaten upon.   <br>
<br>
9. If you had the opportunity to place yourself higher on a mob's aggro list and avoided that opportunity, out of stubbornness then you're a jackass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhick>Rhick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/03 5:42:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Show me the money</span><hr size=1> Frodlin,<br>
