<br>
Now, I'm sold!  Mashing is bad, down with mashing!<br>
<br>
Seriously, by only hitting Taunt when a mob turns away from me, I have dramatically improved my agro management in groups.  Having Taunt un-greyed and ready to go the second the mob spins has saved more caster's lives than I can count over the last few weeks.  Resisting the urge to taunt if the mob is already agroed on me has had a noticable effect on how well I can maintain agro.<br>
<br>
Of course, everyone in the group still has to do their part, agro management is a team effort, and there is still the &quot;taunt failed&quot; factor, but by and large, people who group with me regularly have noticed, and commented on, my improved agro control. <p>-Bumamgar, 65th Warrior</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bumbleroot>Bumbleroot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/27/03 3:50:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Brussel sprouts taste worse.</span><hr size=1> I mash, have little problems keeping aggro during a fight. Or MTing a boss mob. <br>
If I hit taunt, keep attacking mob then I lose taunt, I need to regain aggro. When I hit taunt, keep attacking and don't lose taunt, I will up myself on the aggro list again the next time taunt comes available. If I lose taunt for 1 second after I gain aggro, I'm going to need to get aggro again in 5 seconds or whatever timer on taunt is anyways. If I don't lose aggro, then hitting taunt again helps me keep my aggro. Once mob is on me, it doesn't stray from me too much. I don't have that problem of the mob turning away often. Thats because I constantly am hitting the taunt button. It appears everyone who says you need to taunt the mob as it turns away have the mob turning away from them. This doesn't happen too often from me, and because I mash, when it doesn happen, I get the aggro back quickly.<br>
